EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to governmental entities; requiring certain units of
government of this State to accept certain forms of
payment; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill requires, with certain exceptions, each officer, agency, branch, board,
2 commission, department, division, bureau, district, city, county or other political
3 subdivision or unit of government of this State to accept from a business entity as
4 payment for any fee, tax or other debt, payment by debit card, credit card, check or
5 electronic transfer of money.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 237 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, each
4 governmental agency shall accept from a business entity as
5 payment for any fee, tax or other debt to the governmental agency
6 payment by debit card, credit card, check or electronic transfer of
7 money.
8 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to payments
9 made:
10 (a) Pursuant to NRS 353.1467;
11 (b) To the Department of Taxation pursuant to paragraph (b)
12 of subsection 1 of NRS 360A.040;
